```
These loggers are not fully initialized and will induce a significant latency upon initial use. This is highly undesirable in many cases (e.g. in an EventHandler). Consequently, a new utility method is proposed:

```
public final class LoogerFactoryUtil {

  public static Logger .getAndInitializeLogger(Class<?> clazz) {
    Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(clazz);
    logger.isDebugEnabled();
    return logger;
  }

}

